description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Based: Rotations are based across Essex covering a range of clinical specialities&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GRADE: Band 5&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HOURS: 37.5 per week&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SALARY RANGE : £24,907 - £30,615 per annum &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic and motivated occupational therapists to join our popular and well established rotational scheme which Essex Partnership NHS University Trust operates in partnership with other local trusts such as Basildon and Thurrock University Hospitals Trust and North East London Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a wide and ever changing range of rotations across different care groups in community and in-patient settings for adults, older people, adolescents and children, depending on rotation, in mental health, learning disabilities, paediatrics, general medicine, care of the elderly and stroke in community and in-patient settings. The rotation offers individuals opportunities to develop skills and knowledge in both mental and physical health and may therefore be of interest to newly qualified occupational therapists and qualifying students, as well as occupational therapists wishing to expand their areas of expertise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A preceptorship programme is in place for those in their first year of qualification linked to professional supervision and appraisal, a peer led band 5 staff support group and a wide range of CPD opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;“We will consider applications from students qualifying this summer and in January 2021.”&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Season Ticket Loans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts for staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent Training facilities and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work bank shifts and expand knowledge and experience in other areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary Sacrifice schemes including lease cars and Cycle to Work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Buying and Selling annual leave scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;sharon.rautenbach@nhs.net or 07904163941&lt;/p&gt;
